review_blob: Golden amber, transparent with a thick frothy white head. Yeasty lager aroma, hints of citrus. Champagne flavour, tart, citrusy flavours. Sour aftertaste. Not too bad.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Highway 128 Blood Orange Gose

review_blob: Brown to black colour, thickish beige head. Malty aroma. Quite smoky, but taste seems a little empty. Nice bitter after taste.
beer_name: Hawkers / Edge / KAIJU! / Evil Twin / Baird Inappropriate Touching

review_blob: Lovely opaque orange amber with fair carbonation and a frothy white head. Hoppy, almost fruity aroma is masked somewhat by the foam. Sour, almost vinegar like flavour, but not unpleasant. Very nice.
Clear Amber colouring, thick white head. Fruity aroma. Bitter fruit taste, cloying after taste.
Very dark beer, red tinges coffee coloured head sticks around. Smoky, sweet caramel aroma, quite light. Sour wheat with a caramel smoke touch. Cloying and smokey on the aftertaste.
Red gold, slightly opaque with a creamy head. Lovely aroma, almost chocolate. Very malty. Thick and satisfying in the mouth, leaves a caramel type aftertaste. Its a damn good beer.
beer_name: Anderson Valley Boont Barl Bourbon Barrel Amber Ale

review_blob: Reddish amber, minimal head. Malty caramel aroma. Malty flavour. A bit thin. Not much on the aftertaste. Fairly average.
Coppery colour, thin white head. Immediately funky aroma when poured. A little empty, hints of caramel, no real aftertaste aside from a slight bitterness. Not fantastic.
beer_name: Matilda Bay Ruby Tuesday Amber Ale

review_blob: Amber colour, thin white head. As beery as it gets! Sweet and floral aroma. Its sweet, but with almost a bitter finish. I find it difficult to distinguish ingredients, but it is tasty.
Golden brown colour, no head to speak of. Hoppy aroma. Bitter, but too much. Actually quite warming. Not too bad.
beer_name: Lost Coast 25th Silver Anniversary Belgian Ale

review_blob: Beautiful smoky aroma, coffee.Thick and black, with a small ringlet for a head. Hoppy! Big hoppy, bitter hit. Really sticks round. I like it!
beer_name: Renaissance Enlightenment Series Fresh Hopped Black the RIPA

review_blob: Light honey colour thick white head. Happy aroma. A little bitter, tangy after taste. Fruity.
Pours black with a frothy biege head. Strong chocolate and nut aroma. Big sour hit, smoky overtones. Very tasty.
Darkish amber colour with little head to speak of. Strong flowery hops to the nose. Bitter and hoppy, quite dry. Leaves a cloying, bitter after taste. Its ok.
beer_name: James Squire Hop Thief 6 Simcoe & Columbus

review_blob: Dark and opaque, no head and no ringlet to speak of. Coffee and cocoa on the aroma. Chocolate flavour, really strong fantastic - after taste is sweet and cloying
Sweet fruity aroma. Ruby dark. Sweet tangy, with a bitter after taste. Its decent.
Darkish amber, minimal white head. Light wheat aroma, smells hoppy. Slightly sweet with wheat - actually pretty good. Bitter on the after taste - great summer beer.
beer_name: Hopper Whitman Summer Brew Pale Ale

review_blob: A lovely, bright ale. Not world class mind you, but the kind of beer youll happily be handed after a day in the sun.
beer_name: James Squire The Constable Copper Ale

review_blob: Clear golden ale. White head. VERY hoppy aroma. I swear, this beer smells like it has weed in it..
beer_name: Mountain Goat The Delmont West Coast IPA

review_blob: Lovely fruity aroma. Clear amber. White head. lots of fruit and hops. Delightful.
Honey gold, white head. Wheat aroma. Spicy pepper kick, a bit light on. Smoked? Not bad.
Oaky chocolate aroma on this cola black beer. Coffee taste, quite light. A little empty on the pallet. Not a bad drop.
Hazy gold with a thick white frothy head, almost fruity aroma (can you say you SMELL bitter?), Bitter, hoppy taste with an almost smokey after taste. Not bad, easy to drink.
Golden amber colour, cloudy with a thick white head. Bitter and cloying, quite hoppy. Not bad - does the job.
Dark brown, thick biege head. Coffee aroma. Deep coffee and slight chocolate taste. Smokey. absolutely delicious. Love it.
Nice fruity aroma. Hazy golden amber. Ok. Was drunk when I tried this, cant offer a lot of opinion. It was pretty decent, certainly had worse.
beer_name: Mash Brewing Illustrated Ale Series Grasscutter

review_blob: Passionfruit is strong in the aroma. Golden honey colour, no head to speak of. Sweet, fruit juice flavour - very nice, but is it beer?
Pours a burgundy red with a beige head. Floral, hoppy aroma. Bitter fruit, nice cloying sensation, really hangs around the back of the mouth. Good drop.
Clear straw colour. White head. Funky aroma. Thin, bland beer. This is not very good.
Hazy amber, mid white head. Lots of fruit in the aroma, smells almost like punch. Bitter, fruity. Lovely cloying sensation - I like it.
beer_name: 4 Pines Keller Door Single Hop Series Calypso

review_blob: Clear gold colour, fluffy white head. floral aroma, bit wheaty. Pleasant bitter flavour. Its ok.
Reddish brown, clear with a bit of carbonation. Thick creamy head. Sweet and fruity aroma. Nice bitter taste, cloying finish. Not bad.
Brownish red with a creamy beige head. Sweet fruit and wheat aroma (not too wheaty). Lovely light sweet flavour. A great summer beer. A bit light, but regardless a solid drop.
Clear gold, carbonated. White head. Light wheaty aroma. Almost smoky, quite unusual for the style. Leaves a husky aftertaste - not bad.

Dark chocolate colour, almost black. Nice frothy head, a little unusual for the style. Chocolate coffee aroma. Almost an iced coffee texture, not as thick and string as most porters, but nice. Mocca after taste - nice, I like it.
Clear golden red, small white head. Strong floral aroma. Big thick hops kick with a fruity background. Nice beer - much enjoyed.
Roasted gold colour. Floral aroma. Nice bitter taste. Drunk on Christmas Day!
Black with beige head. Smoked and fruity aroma. Smoky bitterness, leaves a long after taste. Nice.
Light cola colour, thin beige head. Chocolate and roasted nut aroma. Tangy coffee, a bit thin. Its actually not bad - Im just not sure its a Porter.
beer_name: Ass Kisser Bourbon Barrel Aged Smoked Porter

review_blob: Cola colour with a brown head that dissipates into a ringlet. Roasted coffee and nuts to the aroma. Strong and bitter, really cloying - quite nice though.
Dark brown, ruby and cloudy. Minimal white head. Malty roasted aroma. Strong alcohol and roasted flavour. Very tart. Nice.
Hazy, cloudy champagne colouring. Frothy mid white head. Fruity complex aroma. Herb and fruit flavour; deep - quite like it.
Clear gold, moderate carbonation and little head. Strong mango aroma. Sweet and cloying; like a cordial almost. Not great.
Dark orange and hazy, minimal white head. Strong fruit and malt aroma. strong bitter fruit and malt flavour, warming and sticks to the back of the throat. Nice.
beer_name: Moon Dog Lando Kardashian Tripel IPA

review_blob: Dark chocolate with a thick beige/brown head. Aroma is light due to the head, but malty and smokey. Smoked chocolate and nut. Lovely drop.
beer_name: 3 Ravens / Bacchus / Holgate / Moo Brew The Congress

review_blob: Cloudy red gold, minimal head. Fruity hops aroma. Strong hops flavour, bitter after taste - not too bad at all.
Hazy ruby red. Creamy beige head. Big malty aroma. Bitter malts, really gets into the back of the tongue. Warming and long lasting after taste.
beer_name: Holgate Brewhouse / Ngne  Half A World Away

review_blob: Creamy honey gold with white head. Fruity aroma, a bit smoky. Bitter fruit, a bit tropical. Not bad.
beer_name: Ass Kisser Royal Donk Double IPA

review_blob: Dark cola colour, thick and with a creamy dark head. Sour roasted flavour, coffee and oak. Lovely beer.

Pours a light golden colour, a little hazy with moderate carbonation and a small but bright white head. Wheaty aroma with a sweet touch. Bitter, light flavour. Not terrible, doesnt have that funky metal taste, but a very light on beer.
